alerts.headline: Flood Warning issued May 27 at 8:32PM CDT until June 2 at 7:00AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA
alerts.description:
...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Texas...

Black Cypress Bayou At Jefferson affecting Marion and Cass
Counties.

For the Black Cypress Bayou...including Jefferson...Minor flooding
is forecast.

* WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast.

* WHERE...Black Cypress Bayou at Jefferson.

* WHEN...From late Saturday night to Monday morning.

* IMPACTS...At 13.0 feet, Lowland flooding will affect mainly timber
resources.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 8:00 PM CDT Tuesday the stage was 9.8 feet.
- Bankfull stage is 13.0 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 13.0
feet early Sunday morning. It will then fall below flood
stage early Sunday afternoon.
- Flood stage is 13.0 feet.
- Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of
13.6 feet on 12/23/2013.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
alerts.areaDesc: Cass, TX; Marion, TX

alerts.headline: Flood Advisory issued May 27 at 11:33PM CDT until May 28 at 2:45AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX
alerts.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of west central Texas, including the following
counties, Concho, Irion, Schleicher and Tom Green.

* WHEN...Until 245 AM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 1132 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. flooding is ongoing or expected to begin
shortly in the advisory area. Between 1 and 2 inches of rain
have fallen.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
San Angelo, Mertzon, Christoval, Lake Nasworthy, Twin Buttes
Reservoir, Goodfellow Air Force Base, Wall, Knickerbocker,
Tankersley, O.C. Fisher Reservoir, San Angelo State Park,
Veribest, Vancourt, Grape Creek, Sherwood, Mereta, Arden,
Eola, Lowake and Us-67 Near The Irion-Tom Green County Line.
- This includes the following Low Water Crossings...
College Hills and Millbrook, Southwest Blvd and Loop 306,
Jackson From Knickerbocker to South Bryant, Howard and
Webster, FM 2334 crossing Ninemile Creek, RM 853 crossing Dry
Draw, FM 1692 crossing Concho River, FM 1692 crossing Sales
Branch, Ranch Road 853 crossing east Rocky Creek and FM 2334
crossing Dry Lipan Creek.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
alerts.areaDesc: Concho, TX; Irion, TX; Schleicher, TX; Tom Green, TX

alerts.description:
